{"key":"post-14887768","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>14887768</id>\n<content>After filling the jar, take a wooden spoon or block of wood and whack the sides of the jar a few times.&amp;nbsp; This will settle the mix.&amp;nbsp; Add more if necessary and then top off with the dry verm layer.&amp;nbsp; Tap again and top off the dry verm.&amp;nbsp; If you put the jar lid rubber side up, the shape of the lid allows you to pile the verm up a bit above the edge of the glass.&amp;nbsp; This should fix the settling problem.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>14887671</prev>\n<first>9501406</first>\n<last>14887768</last>\n<when>1312776384</when>\n<utime>08/08/11 07:06 AM</utime>\n</post>"}